4.0. Text Preprocessing¶

4.1. Cleaning Text¶

4.1.1. Function to Clean Text¶

In [64]:
def clean_text(Message):
    text = Message.lower()  #To lowercase
    text = re.sub(r"\\n", " ", text)  #newline characters with space
    text = re.sub(r"[^a-zA-Z0-9\s]", "", text)  # Remove punctuation and special characters
    text = re.sub(r"\s+", " ", text).strip()  # Remove extra whitespace
    return text

results = []

7.0. Model Metrics Function¶

In [71]:
def evaluate_model(name, model):
    model.fit(X_train, y_train)
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    metrics = {
        'Algorithm': name,
        'Accuracy': accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred),
        'Precision': precision_score(y_test, y_pred),
        'Recall': recall_score(y_test, y_pred),
        'F1-Score': f1_score(y_test, y_pred),
        'Dataset': 'Test Set'
    }
    results.append(metrics)
    print(f"{name} Metrics: {metrics}")

8.0. Cross Validation Function¶

In [72]:
def cross_validate_model(name, model, X, y, cv=5):
    skf = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=cv, shuffle=True, random_state=42)
    accuracy = cross_val_score(model, X, y, scoring='accuracy', cv=skf).mean()
    precision = cross_val_score(model, X, y, scoring='precision', cv=skf).mean()
    recall = cross_val_score(model, X, y, scoring='recall', cv=skf).mean()
    f1 = cross_val_score(model, X, y, scoring='f1', cv=skf).mean()

    metrics = {
        'Algorithm': f"{name} (CV)",
        'Accuracy': accuracy,
        'Precision': precision,
        'Recall': recall,
        'F1-Score': f1,
        'Dataset': 'Cross-Validation'
    }
    results.append(metrics)
    print(f"{name} Cross-Validation Metrics: {metrics}")

16.1. Function to predict Spam¶

In [99]:
# Function to predict if a message is spam or not
def predict_spam(message, model):
    cleaned_message = clean_text(message)
    vectorized_message = vectorizer.transform([cleaned_message])
    prediction = model.predict(vectorized_message)[0]
    return "Spam" if prediction == 1 else "Not Spam"
